Bob++

Authors:
    Bertrand Le Cun, 
    François Galea 
    Pascal Vander-Swalmen
    Tarek Menouer

Introduction
============

The Bob++ Library is a set of C++ classes. Its goal is to allow easy
implementation of sequential and parallel search algorithms (Branch and X,
Divide and conquer, etc) to solve your own problems.

Features
========

 * Object Oriented
 * Several Search Algorithms User Algorithms
 * Automatic Options and Parameters Handling ( see The Options Module).
 * Error Handling
 * transparent parallelizations (POSIX Thread, MPI, Kaapi)

More information, visit the official project website:
http://forge.prism.uvsq.fr/projects/bobpp

